Package morpion

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Ai
    Represent the ai model manager and game data
    Ai.Data
    Represent the list of played moves from each player during a game
    Ai.Data.Move
    Represent a move played by a player on the grid
    Ai.Model
    Represent the ai model
    AnimationFactory
    Has the responsibility to create and give access to every animation used in the main interface
    Controller
    Is responsible for the realisation of the application use cases (and so the synchronization between the entity and the view)
    Ent
    Represent the entity, the state of the game at a certain moment
    Ent.Grid
    Represent a grid with a fixed dimension
    Main
    Represent the application launcher
    RES
    Is responsible for giving easy access to resources (images)
    TaskConfiguring<Void>
    Is responsible for detecting whenever the configuration file has changed and informing the learning thread
    TaskLearning<Void>
    Is responsible for making the ai model learn about new moves
    View
    Is responsible for handling events, calling the controller use cases and playing animations
    View.Grid
    Represent the grid in the view
    View.Menu
    Represent the menu in the view
    View.Turn
    Represent the turn in the view
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Difficulty
    Represent the different level of difficulty in the game
    Mode
    Represent the game modes
    Player
    Represent the players
    Row
    Represent a row in a grid
    Square
    Represent a square, meaning its content, in the grid
